    <note>Liu(2) Su(3) [13241] According to Luo(1) Yuan [17214], who composed the funerary inscription in place of the father, Chen(1) Gao [24250], of Su(3)'s son-in-law, Chen(1) Chongnian [24252], the Chen had been intermarried with the Liu(2) (shiyin) since a Chen(1) became the wife of Su's 6th generation ancestor, Shi [1226]. The first born Chen, educated all five sons, who all earned the jinshi degree and was known as the 'Mother of the five jun [zi].' See her entry in CBD, 5, 3844. Luo Yuan, WJ, 4.38-39. CBD, 5, 3984.</note>
